<div class="home-banner" style="background-image: url(<%= image_path('background.svg') %>)">
  <%= image_tag 'logo-teacher.png', class: 'logo' %>
  <div class="banner-title">
    <h1>Homework organisation made <strong>easy</strong>, for <strong>everyone</strong>.</h1>
  </div>
  <div class="banner-sign-up">
    <div class="banner-form">
      <div class="login-banner-main">
      <h3>Log in</h3>
      </div>
      <div class="login-banner-entry">
      <%= simple_form_for(resource, as: resource_name, url: session_path(resource_name)) do |f| %>
        <div class="form-group-email">
           <!--  <input type="email" class="form-control" id="inputEmail" placeholder="Email Address"> -->
            <%= f.input :email,
              required: false,
              autofocus: true,
              input_html: { autocomplete: "email" } %>
        </div>
        <div class="form-group-password">
              <%= f.input :password,
              required: false,
              input_html: { autocomplete: "current-password" } %>
        </div>
        <%= f.button :submit, "Let's go", class: "btn-blue-login" %>
      <% end %>
    </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
<div class="container">
  <div class="home-image-display">
    <h2>How does it work?</h2>
    <div class="home-info-box">
      <div class="home-info guardian-info">
        <%= image_tag 'facebook-img.png', class: "home-page-image" %>
        <h3>For the guardians</h3>
        <p>Homework monitor allows you to see the homework set by all your childrens teachers, in real time. No more wondering what homework has been set, missed instructions or awkward conversations about final marks. Everything you need to know abut each classes homework, all in one place, for all of your children. </p>
      </div>
      <div class="home-info student-info">
        <%= image_tag 'facebook-img.png', class: "home-page-image" %>
        <h3>For the students</h3>
        <p>Often forget what homework you have to complete today or what was set in your class this morning? Homework monitor is the place to check what your teachers have set, see all instructions and check your marks after you have handed it in. </p>
      </div>
      <div class="home-info teacher-info">
        <%= image_tag 'facebook-img.png', class: "home-page-image" %>
        <h3>For the teachers</h3>
        <p>Easily create, set and mark homework all in one place, for all your classes. Communicate directly with guardians with extra notes and make sure they have seen the final notes and follow up comments. The app to save you time and stress.  </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>


